<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="165" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,782,2033]" pageId="14" pageNumber="165">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,365,890,916]" pageId="14" pageNumber="165">Redescription</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[382,468,891,917]" pageId="14" pageNumber="165">Length</emphasis>
(pronotum and elytra) of males and females 6.9 to 7.1/ 
<quantity box="[1114,1281,891,917]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.7" metricValueMax="8.8" metricValueMin="6.6" pageId="14" pageNumber="165" unit="mm" value="7.7" valueMax="8.8" valueMin="6.6">6.6 to 8.8 mm</quantity>
, respectively. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,289,927,953]" pageId="14" pageNumber="165">Integument</emphasis>
bright, varying from dark brown to reddish-brown. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[893,999,927,953]" pageId="14" pageNumber="165">Rostrum</emphasis>
about 1.7 times longer than length of pronotum, about 6.2 times longer than apical width of rostrum in females, and about 5.05 times longer in males.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,782,2033]" pageId="14" pageNumber="165">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,247,999,1025]" pageId="14" pageNumber="165">Thorax.</emphasis>
Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[384,463,999,1025]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="15.[151,250,978,1002]" captionTargetBox="[160,1424,247,948]" captionTargetId="figure-40@15.[151,1436,237,954]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 7. Holotype Heilus rufescens, female. A. dorsal view. B. lateral view. C. labels. The copyright of images belongs to NHRS." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4414700" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4414700/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="165">Figs. 7</figureCitation>
A–B) about 1.4 times wider than long, rounded sides, densely covered with rounded granules with small punctation at apical margin in center, densely covered with yellow and whitish scales, with three bands of oblong, whitish or yellowish scales, two on sides and one at center of pronotum, distributed from base to median region. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[415,491,1107,1133]" pageId="14" pageNumber="165">Elytra</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[508,585,1107,1133]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="15.[151,250,978,1002]" captionTargetBox="[160,1424,247,948]" captionTargetId="figure-40@15.[151,1436,237,954]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 7. Holotype Heilus rufescens, female. A. dorsal view. B. lateral view. C. labels. The copyright of images belongs to NHRS." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4414700" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4414700/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="165">Figs. 7</figureCitation>
A–B) about 1.5 times longer than wide, oblique granules, slightly elevated, each one with short scale, very distinct at apex, inserted into interstriae, more condensed in humeral region, smaller and sparse granules in apical region; densely covered with setae ranging from light yellow to dark brown, median region with irregular macula of dark brown scales between striae 2 and 5, with transverse band of yellowish setae on posterior margin, and more condensed setae in apical region; moderately coarse elytral striae, finer at apex, flat interstriae. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[279,452,1286,1313]" pageId="14" pageNumber="165">Male genitalia</emphasis>
. Median lobe of aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[773,874,1287,1313]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1531,1555]" captionTargetBox="[161,1436,191,1499]" captionTargetId="figure-20@28.[151,1436,181,1508]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 18. Aedeagus. A. Heilus inaequalis, dorsal view. B. Heilus inaequalis, lateral view. C. Heilus pupillatus. D. Heilus tuberculosus. E. Heilus rufescens. F. Heilus freyreissi. G. Heilus myops. H. Heilus faldermanni. I. Heilus ochrifer. J. Heilus fasciculatus. K. Heilus iniquus. L. Heilus bistigma. Legends: median lobe (ml), internal sac sclerite (sc), median lobe apodemes (mla)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4414722" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4414722/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="165">Fig. 18E</figureCitation>
) with straight apex, with few setae; median lobe apodemes about 2.2 times longer than median lobe. Internal sac armed with bifurcate sclerite, with elongate spicules on sides (
<figureCitation box="[255,359,1359,1385]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1600,1624]" captionTargetBox="[161,1426,187,1566]" captionTargetId="figure-19@29.[151,1436,181,1576]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 19. Internal sac sclerite. A. Heilus inaequalis. B. Heilus pupillatus. C. Heilus tuberculosus. D. Heilus rufescens. E. Heilus freyreissi. F. Heilus myops. G. Heilus faldermanni. H. Heilus ochrifer. I. Heilus fasciculatus. J. Heilus iniquus. K. Heilus bistigma." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4414724" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4414724/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="165">Fig. 19D</figureCitation>
). Tegmen (
<figureCitation box="[481,582,1359,1385]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1023,1047]" captionTargetBox="[156,1430,187,994]" captionTargetId="figure-21@30.[151,1436,181,999]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 20. Tegmen. A. Heilus inaequalis. B. Heilus pupillatus. C. Heilus tuberculosus. D. Heilus rufescens. E. Heilus freyreissi. F. Heilus myops. G. Heilus faldermanni. H. Heilus ochrifer. I. Heilus fasciculatus. J. Heilus iniquus. K. Heilus bistigma. Legends: dorsal lobe (ld), manubrium (m)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4414726" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4414726/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="165">Fig. 20D</figureCitation>
) with manubrium about 1.8 times longer than dorsal lobes. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1241,1437,1358,1385]" pageId="14" pageNumber="165">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[160,263,1395,1421]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="31.[151,250,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[161,1423,191,1873]" captionTargetId="figure-19@31.[151,1436,181,1886]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURE 21. Female genitalia. A. Heilus inaequalis. B. Heilus pupillatus. C. Heilus tuberculosus. D. Heilus rufescens. E. Heilus freyreissi. F. Heilus myops. G. Heilus faldermanni. H. Heilus ochrifer. I. Heilus fasciculatus. J. Heilus iniquus. K. Heilus bistigma. Legends: coxite (cx), styli (st), common oviduct (co), bursa copulatrix (bc), spermathecal duct (spd), spermathecal capsule (sp), spermathecal gland (spg)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4414728" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4414728/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="165">Fig. 21D</figureCitation>
). Coxites longer than wide, with short setae close to insertion of styli; styli longer than wide, with elongate setae at apex. Spermathecal duct short inserted into final portion of bursa copulatrix. Spermathecal capsule (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="32.[151,250,1947,1971]" captionTargetBox="[184,1403,713,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-268@32.[173,1414,705,1923]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURE 22. Spermathecal capsule. A. Heilus inaequalis. B. Heilus pupillatus. C. Heilus tuberculosus. D. Heilus rufescens. E. Heilus freyreissi. F. Heilus myops. G. Heilus faldermanni. H. Heilus ochrifer. I. Heilus fasciculatus; J. Heilus iniquus; K. Heilus bistigma. Legends: cornu (cr), collum (cl), ramus (ra)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4414730" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4414730/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="165">Fig. 22D</figureCitation>
) slightly curved, 
<emphasis box="[398,474,1467,1493]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="165">collum</emphasis>
narrow, 
<emphasis box="[574,644,1467,1492]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="165">ramus</emphasis>
well-developed, robust, and rough, 
<emphasis box="[1050,1115,1467,1492]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="165">cornu</emphasis>
subtriangular. Spermathecal gland elongate, enlarged at base, narrowing to apex.
</paragraph>
