<subSubSection lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="166" pageId="14" pageNumber="165" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,782,2033]" lastBlockId="15.[151,1436,151,213]" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="166" pageId="14" pageNumber="165">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1935,1961]" pageId="14" pageNumber="165">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Kuschel" authorityYear="1955" box="[321,507,1935,1961]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Heilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="165" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufescens">
<emphasis box="[321,507,1935,1961]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="165">Heilus rufescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is one of the smallest South American species of the genus, measuring less than 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.9" pageId="14" pageNumber="165" unit="mm" value="8.9">8.9 mm</quantity>
. The main characters that distinguish 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Kuschel" authorityYear="1955" box="[630,772,1971,1997]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Heilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="165" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufescens">
<emphasis box="[630,772,1971,1997]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="165">H. rufescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
